{"author":{"id":"bf52274e4b8baa03d436abcc532c02b6a719b9a772a7e952e18fcc8627570e5f"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1782087841,"nonce":"pTuBsk7ig/NKbDbqe2ynw2gF3gc=","title":"Type parsing of inputs/outputs in external CWL workflows too simplistic","message":"`cwl-workflow` assumes inputs/outputs in external CWL workflows are primitive types. As such, it cannot handle more complex types such as vector types, optional types, etc. Implement a full type parser. Here is a sample external CWL workflow with an optional string type for which `cwl-workflow` fails:\n```yaml\ncwlVersion: v1.2\nclass: CommandLineTool\nbaseCommand: echo\ninputs:\n  message:\n    type:\n      - string\n      - null\n    inputBinding:\n      position: 1\noutputs: {}\n```","files":null}]}